FBIS3-45329 "drchi011_n_94006" FBIS-CHI-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 Economic & Agricultural Beijing To Issue $1 Billion in Bonds in U.S. OW1501144494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1415 GMT 15 Jan 94 OW1501144494 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, January 15 (XINHUA) -- China's Ministry of Finance has registered in the Securities Exchange Commission of the United States to issue one billion U.S. dollars-worth of global bonds. Led by Merrill Lynch and Co., Inc., some world major security companies and banks will underwrite the bonds in the United States, Europe and Asia. Jin Renqing, China's deputy finance minister, said that this was the first time for the Chinese Government to issue global bonds and enter the U.S. capital market.
